Minute Entry for proceedings held before Chief Magistrate Judge Justo Arenas : AUSA Timothy Henwood and Atty. Carlos Calderon-Garnier were present.Arraignment as to Woady Arrindel (2) Count 1,2,3,4,14 held on 10/25/2006. Defendant stated his true name as Woady Augri Lopez. PONG entered. Bail Hearing as to Woady Arrindel held on 10/25/2006. Counsel proffered that defendant was extradicted, has two (2) brothers in the U.S. mainland, and would reserve the right to reopen the matter of bail. The Court finds defendant to lack ties in the community and is a risk of flight. Therefore, defendant is ordered detained without bail pending trial. Order will follow. (Court Reporter FTR, CI: Edna Brayfield, PTSO: Evelyn Jimenez.) (br, ) (Entered: 10/27/2006)

Minute Entry for proceedings held before Chief Magistrate Judge Justo Arenas :Arraignment as to Geronimo Confesor-Mendoza (3) Count 1,2,3,4,5,6,14,15 held on 10/25/2006. PONG entered. Defense counsel requested to hold the bail today. The Govn't had no objection. Bail Hearing as to Geronimo Confesor-Mendoza held on 10/25/2006. Defense counsel proffered that defendant does not have ties in the community. The Court finds defendant to be a risk of flight and ordered defendant detained without bail pending trial. Order will follow. The Government requested an order to PTSO to view the pretrial report. Defense counsel concurred. The Court granted the request to allow the parties view the pretrial report by PTSO. Deft. remains u/c. (Court Reporter FTR, CI: Edna Brayfield.) (br, ) (Entered: 10/27/2006)

ORDER granting 586 Motion for Extension of Time as to Francisco Mexuyam Lopez- Giraldo (5). NO FURTHER EXTENSIONS SHALL BE GRANTED. The Court reminds counsel that having too many cases to handle is not an excuse to fail to comply with this Courts Order. The Court, consistently, has refused to accept such excuses. See. Mndez v. Banco Popular de P.R., 900 F.2d 4,8 (1st Cir. 1990); Pinero Schroeder v. FNMA, 574 F.2d 1117,1118 (1st Cir. 1978). The fact that an attorney has other fish to fry 1s not an acceptable reason for disregarding a court order. Chamorro v. Puerto Rican Cars INC, 304, F.3d 1, 5 (1st Cir., 2002). This mandate to the undersigned means: Too many fish to fry is no excuse to fail to comply. Change of Plea Hearing is set for July 24, 2009 at 9:00 a.m. Change of plea motion shall be filed by July 23, 2009. Jury Trial is set for August 3, 2009 at 9:30 am. NO CONTINUANCES SHALL BE GRANTED. IT IS SO ORDERED. Signed by Judge Daniel R. Dominguez on 06/24/2009. (om) (Entered: 06/25/2009)

ORDER: denying 655 Motion for Reconsideration as to Joan Garcia-Gonzalez (12); denying 658 Motion for Reconsideration as to Joan Garcia-Gonzalez (12); denying 709 Motion for Return of Property/PostTrial as to Joan Garcia-Gonzalez (12). The Customs and Border Protection Office of Fines and Penalties administratively forfeited the amount of $773,962.00 on June 22, 2006. The records reflect that the property was abandoned at the time of the seizure. Defendant is therefore restrained from requesting the return of any property seized and administratively forfeited pursuant to Rule 41(g). Moreover, on February 3, 2005, Defendant Joan Garcia-Gonzalez voluntarily and in writing stated that the currency was not his, abandoned the seized property, and waived any and all kinds of actions and claims. See Docket No. 718, Exhibit A. For these reasons, the Court DENIES Defendant's Motion for Reconsideration regarding the Court's Order [Docket No. 655], Defendant's Second Motion for Reconsideration regarding Court's Order [Docket No. 658], and Defendant's Motion for Return of Property/PostTrial Requesting Final Disposition [Docket No. 709]. Signed by Judge Daniel R. Dominguez on 4/4/2018. (MES) (Entered: 04/04/2018)
